	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Aug 17th 5:22 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.69]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Enchanters can be solo'd with no problems from lvl 1 to lvl 35.&nbsp;&nbsp;It just requires changing tactics as mobs get tougher.<br><br>The first 10-15 levels or so is basically, summon a pet, buff yourself and the pet and go kill a mob together(spells and weapon).  Wisp Island is a good place for this as is West Karana.<br><br>Pretty soon the mobs will start to hit too hard to melee.  At lvl 16, we get our first DD.  After buffing yourself and your pet, go find a mob you want to kill.  Mez it, debuff it, med.  When you are ready(not necessarily full mana), blast it, take a hit and let the pet engage...move away a bit and med(the mob will slowly move towards you).  Once your pet gets in the danger HP range, start blasting so that the mob is totally infatuated with you...if you get in danger, run away and jump a couple of times, it will stay focused on you and not turn on your pet OR you can use fear(i don't recommend fear kiting as its own strat, because we have no way of slowing the mobs.  fear kiting is a team technique as far as enchanters are concerned).  This strat can be used from lvl 16 to lvl 22 or so.  Places to solo are north and east karana and lake rathetear.<br><br>It is at this point that enchanters become the most powerful solo class in the game.  The charm spell is finally useful enough to last for a good duration.  Find two mobs you want to kill:  <br>1.)Tashani 1 to pull it, color flux, charm it.<br>2.)/pet attack the other mob, tashani the other mob and root it...you MUST keep it rooted.<br>3.)Let them duke it out...if the charm breaks, color flux and charm again(it'll go right back to fighting)...if the root breaks, the mob will still hate your pet so rerooting is no prob...if they both break hope that color flux is enough to get them off you, and do your favorite enchanter escape manuever(mez, mem blur, RUN, whatever).<br><br>The charm technique works best with mobs that either, are not in agro range of each other OR don't care if each other is attacked.<br><br>This technique can be used on even cons and yellows indefinately.  SOW or jboots are VERY helpful in escaping however they are not required as long as you fight mobs that aren't faster than you are normally.<br><br>The reason I said that enchanters become the most powerful solo class with charm is because we can kill even 2 mobs with about 50% mana left over(as long as you kill the target and then your pet afterwards).  No other class can claim this.  Happy hunting.<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
