<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99116270170568></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99116270170568><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=99116270170568>RE: Soloing Dual Spawns...</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=99116270170568#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=58627><span id= >Rhiaprexus</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>3 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, May 29th 2:58 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Yesterday was a sad day... these rangers are now green to me (they are level 30, every time).&nbsp;&nbsp;I started killing them with an enchanter partner at level 30, and I am now level 42.  They are awesome experience (remember treants?  better...) and they drop very good loot (usually a couple fine steel weapons that i can sell for 5pp to 6pp each at an inn that is within my casting range, plus up to 4pp - averaging about 12pp per kill).  Interesting that Illia used a charm strategy, i never did that (although i did charm a griffin one time to take out both rangers with ease:).  I would open with a mez, the other would shoot me with an arrow or attack with a spell.  my pet would charge up the hill to it and i would whirl the ranger about halfway down the hill, then hit them with a big DD.  tash if you get resisted.  usually whirl breaks and it runs right at me, so if you can time it right, hit your stun and they will stand infront of  you looking stupid (just like the PC rangers).  back up and when you're spells recover hit your big DD again, all this time your pet is hacking away at it with dual wield and a haste buff.  this is also when the ranger will try to heal itself, so you must stun to interrupt their spell (very important to be mana efficient). if you're not within melee range and you see them casting the blue sparkals, hit them with whirl again.  One more DD and the exp and FS weapons are yours.<br><br>if you are getting resisted throw you CHA buff up, i found that it helps a ton!<br><br>I could first solo these at level 34, though it was a little scary, and one mistake and it's all over.  if you have the means to obtain high poison resist or high fire resist i suggest doing so, crud is nasty, and so is their combust spell.<br><br>I can usually make 250-300pp per hour and about 3 blues per hour killing these (one blue per hour in a hell level).<br><br>Enchanters are the best class to fight these rangers, hands down.  Enchanters can start soloing these at 34, and necros or mages can't even hope to solo these until 38+.  Melee classes have no hope of soloing these except for SK's, but that isnt until about 40 or so when they dont give as much exp. Even if a necro could solo these though level 40, he's only getting 1pp to 2pp per fine steel weapon, and he can't sell them twelve steps away like enchanters can.<br><br>the WC zone is also close, incase you get in trouble, also - you might try illusion halfling to get even more exp, i'm not sure if this works or not, i need to do more testing on it.  any comments on my post are appreciated.<br><br>Also, i bought some nice things from the platinum I earned killing these.  Very easy to stay up on prices since you are in EC.  Int is now 171 and Cha is 205.<br><br>Rhia Gaultheria<br>Level 42 Enchanter<br>Prexus<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
